.TH YADEX 6 $SOURCE_DATE "Yadex $VERSION" \" -*- nroff -*-
.SH NAME
yadex \- Doom/Doom II/Heretic level (wad) editor for X
.SH SYNOPSIS
.BR "yadex \-?" | \-help | \-\-help
.br
.B yadex \-\-version
.br
\fByadex\fP [\fIoptions\fP] [\fIfile\fP ...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Yadex can be used to view, create and modify levels for \fBDoom
alpha\fP, \fBDoom press release pre beta\fP, \fBDoom\fP, \fBDoom
II\fP, \fBUltimate Doom\fP, \fBFinal Doom\fP and \fBHeretic\fP.
It also supports, to a lesser extent, \fBHexen\fP and
\fBStrife\fP.

See \fBREADME\fP for a quick start.
.br
To know what's new in this release, see \fBCHANGES\fP.
.br
The rest of documentation is in \fBdoc/index.html\fP (HTML format).
.SH FILES
.B ./yadex.cfg
.br
.B ~/yadex.cfg
.br
\fIinstall_dir\fB/yadex.cfg\fP
.br
.B /usr/local/etc/yadex.cfg
.br
.B /etc/yadex.cfg

.BI ./ game .ygd
.br
.BI ~/ game .ygd
.br
.IB install_dir / doom .ygd
.br
.BI /usr/local/share/games/ game .ygd
.br
.BI /usr/share/games/ game .ygd
.SH ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
.IP \fBDISPLAY\fP
X11 only. The name of the X display that Yadex will try to connect to.
.IP \fBYADEX_GAME\fB
Indicates the game to use.
Overrides the \fBgame\fP parameter in the config file,
is overridden by the \fB\-g\fP command line option.
.SH APPLICATION RESOURCES
None. Yadex does not use the X resources system.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.ta 3
\fB0\fP	OK.
.br
\fB1\fP	Incorrect invocation.
.br
\fB2\fP	Fatal error.
.SH BUGS
Command line options that take an argument
need to have a space between their argument and themselves.

In certain circumstances, exposures are not handled.
If the Yadex window turns black,
back out by pressing \fBEsc\fP, several times if necessary.

If you edit a level from a file that contains several and save it,
all the other levels from that file are lost.

And many more. See \fBTODO\fP.
